First Lady Michelle Obama will lead the Presidential Delegation to the Opening Ceremonies of the 2012 Summer Olympic Games in London. Mrs. Obama made the announcement at an event celebrating the Olympic Games and her Let's Move! initiative. She hopes that the games will inspire more young people to get active and healthy. Mrs. Obama emphasized the importance of participating and being active, regardless of athletic ability. The White House will announce the official delegates accompanying Mrs. Obama to London in the coming months. Previous First Ladies who have led a Presidential Delegation to the Olympic Games include Laura Bush and Hillary Rodham Clinton.